> Just thinking aloud here: If we had called these request and response instead of spec and status, then we could have had a convention in kubectl that if a thing has request and response, then kubectl should print out the response.

I think we probably want a "show me what came back" flag on `kubectl create` so that users can see how their object was defaulted.

@fabianofranz Want to try to make such a thing?
